In the meantime, to say goodnight we say "oidhche mhath" (pr. oo-ee-khuh vah - the kh sound is pronounced like the 'ch' in Bach or loch)

That's not to say that my pronunciation is magically great (I'm sure I'm butchering half of it), but I just get this feeling bubbling up in my chest of joy & rebellion. Gàidhlig  was almost taken from us. I'm taking it back.

Reconnecting with the language my family used to speak & lost for several generations is such an odd experience. I go through phases of frustration with the spelling because of how I was taught to read, but something in the pronunciation just feels like home.

@orcphilosopher @macca_the_dm Oh absolutely there are always STs who want to basically run vampire superheroes, but as written that's not really what the game is about and I really dislike playing in those games anyway. I'm all about that sweet gaming catharsis, baybeeee!

@macca_the_dm Masks is a fantastic game about teen superheroes, their responsibilities and the social pressures of still being kids surrounded by adults. The mechanic where people can try to change your stats based on their perception of you is really interesting!

@macca_the_dm Hillfolk is a really interesting system for a bickering community and the fact that it can be ported into so many different settings is just really neat! It is less focused on what you are doing and more on the social pressures around your actions.

@macca_the_dm I love Vampire the Masquerade for the personal horror vibes and that you are in fact the monster. I like that humanity is something you're generally supposed to cling to and that being an awful person has consequences!

@macca_the_dm A game called They Became Flesh (sadly not available to purchase but can be downloaded here https://t.co/XAFokStMmZ ) is a great game about playing fallen angels. It's short, to the point & has an interesting mechanic around how miracles are easier the larger scale they are!

20. Paranoid Malk hacker gathered information about her coterie & other NPCs & set up a system that, if she died, all the info would be released to as many kindred in the city as possible. Thankfully this never happened, but oh god - I've not committed many atrocities apparently
@ksandra_br Yuuuuuuup. It was a trainwreck!
19. Because I'm not great at balancing or knowing how my added rules will affect the game I rarely houserule stuff.
18. Homeless Thinblood teenager with the Baby Teeth flaw, having to use Animalism to get her cat familiar to hunt for her.

17. I've had two characters who diablerised their sire's as part of their backstory, but none of my characters have committed diablerie in game. I tend to stick to the idea that it's a major sin and avoid it.
16. The new Lasombra clan curse from 5th edition is great! I love that it no longer work's in their favour!
15. The time my players walked into the room with an artifact keeping a Nosferatu Methuselah in torpor and rolled 7 botches. Shockingly she woke up.
14. @CraigOxbrow, @ksandra_br, @kae_serpent, and @doloresdraws are all fantastic!

13. In a serious game with experienced players I like the game be pretty serious, however that's not to say that comedic moments can't arise and humorous off hand comments are more than welcome. If everything is serious all the time, then the horror doesn't stand out.
12. Not sure if unexpected, but my own experience with ADHD and memory problems spawned the concept for my Malkavian, Beatrycze.

11. I personally enjoy it. I've co-gm'd a crossover campaign (Vamp/Mage) that didn't work as the themes/power scale clashed, but antagonists of other settings can be really fun! Thallain trying to destroy the world? Power hungry mages? Pissed off Garou? Hell yeah!

10. I'm sure there is, no setting that's been around this long with so many writers etc can be perfect, I just can't think of it right- oh wait, Healer Salubri, why do y'all keep eating your sires?! That ain't gonna help you recover, nor prove the whole diablerist claim wrong!
9. I find I rarely make Charisma a dump stat in Vampire. I'm a chatty person and I my favourite part is engaging with PCs and NPCs.
8. Either Int, Str or Stam, depending on the character. I love playing either dumbass characters or weak, noodle-y ones 😂

7. I reference canon characters as a player- had Gangrel character stuck in the body of a child who was very serious academic & rarely smiled, but would fan girl over Beckett at the drop of a hat. As a storyteller I rarely bring in canon characters as I like coming up with my own
6. I have watched some LA by Night which I loved, but sadly my attention span rarely allows for me to watch games for long lengths of time. Thanks ADHD! 🙄

5. Ravnos. I struggle to see past the problematic stereotypes and it makes me pretty uncomfortable. I also struggle to think of interesting Ventrue to play for some reason! NPCs are fine, but for some reason I just draw a blank for personal character concepts!
4. So many choices! As a genderfluid person, Vicissitude's fleshcrafting is very appealing to me for personal usage 😂 but also Animalism. I want all cats to be my friends.

3. I love the Anarchs a lot, but I think I find Camarilla more fun. The traditions, continuous threats of backstabbing and a power structure that you have no hope of climbing? The drama! The aesthetic! *chef's kiss*
